 their own time, we are more likely to get a higher uptake, and higher level of engagement, when we deploy content that aims to improve organisational effectiveness or productivity.  \r\n\r\nWe’re already seeing a marked shift away from traditional e-learning solutions towards the creation of portals which host dynamic content in ways that emulate end-users’ typical online experiences outside the workplace. The challenge that organisations now face is how to increase the effectiveness of these portals and micro-sites. In many respects, the solutions deployed to date are still inferior to external sites. The internet is innovating exponentially and many of these portals are already showing signs of age. \r\n\r\nBy 2017 74% of all internet traffic will be video. People are more excited about watching video or animations than sifting through huge amounts of static content. So why are so many digital learning programmes still taking such a minimalist approach to visual and animated assets? There is still a risk that users will feel coerced into learning rather than truly engaging with the content. It is not only desirable, but absolutely essential, for L&D professionals to innovate and keep pace with wider online trends.\r\n'),(5939,564,'_main_content_area','field_5629ec918a334'),(5940,564,'single_image',''),(5941,564,'_single_image','field_5629ea2db47b2'),(5942,564,'header_image',''),(5943,564,'_header_image','field_5629edc6a3424'),(5944,564,'standfirst_text',''),(5945,564,'_standfirst_text','field_5629ea6d8d729'),(5946,564,'vimeo_id',''),(5947,564,'_vimeo_id','field_5629e91cf9252'),(5948,564,'vimeo_id_two',''),(5949,564,'_vimeo_id_two','field_564b0ac8ebbf4'),(5950,564,'youtube_id',''),(5951,564,'_youtube_id','field_5629e94ef9253'),(5952,564,'_','field_5629e968f9254'),(5953,563,'image_1','199'),(5954,563,'_image_1','field_560ba235a1f37'),(5955,563,'image_2','443'),(5956,563,'_image_2','field_560ba25da1f38'),(5957,563,'image_3','142'),(5958,563,'_image_3','field_560ba27