rough the entire process.  With creative and strategic teams you willl be required to own the project in conjunction with the account teams. \r\n\r\nExperience in being client facing and working with account handling to manage client relationships.   You’ll have excellent attention to detail, negotiation, organisational and administration skills.   Accomplished in motiviating, managing and developing project teams and working with multiple stakeholders.  \r\n\r\nYou will have hands on experience in producing small to large film and motion graphics projects. Ideally you will have a good database of relevant contacts and understanding of industry rules and regulations, casting, location finding, treatments, freelance crewing, knowledge of directors, animators, composers etc. \r\n\r\nExperience in integrated digital projects would be an advantage but not essential however as your knowledge of interactive projects builds your role may expand to include such projects.\r\n\r\nAs an agency highly respected by our clients for our passion and creativity, you’ll need to be able to demonstrate a great portfolio of work spanning film and motion graphics. A ‘can-do’ attitude and great communication skills. If you are a passionate and motivated Creative Digital Producer who wants to work with a great bunch of like minded people then please get in touch now.\r\n\r\nApply at <a href=\"mailto:recruitment@wearetilt.com\">recruitment@wearetilt.com</a>\r\n\r\nClosing date for application is 1st Feb 2016. '),(6918,643,'_main_content_area','field_5629ec918a334'),(6921,645,'image_1','634'),(6922,645,'_image_1','field_560ba235a1f37'),(6923,645,'image_2','635'),(6924,645,'_image_2','field_560ba25da1f38'),(6925,645,'image_3','636'),(6926,645,'_image_3','field_560ba272a1f39'),(6927,645,'image_4','637'),(6928,645,'_image_4','field_560ba279a1f3a'),(6929,645,'main_content_area','Water is something that everyone can relate to. Yet we rarely think about where it comes from, and how far its ancient molecular cocktail has travelled, to be here with us in this small moment - or how it will exist long after we\'re gone. For Elwoood’s Ark, we wanted to create a short film that would approach the subject of water’s journey, and our fragile relationship with it, putting into perspective human existence in the vastness of time and space.\r\n \r\nThe towering brick arches and Noah\'s Ark-like appearance of St Bartholomew\'s church seemed a fitting setting for this story. It is an ever present feature of our daily lives at Tilt - a vast solitary relic from a flattened Victorian neibourhood that is now the heart of Brighton\'s blooming digital community. The huge interior – the largest nave in England - offered an amazing opportunity in which to grow a digital lightening storm, released from the hands of a child.\r\n \r\nThe film is shot on in 6k RED cinema to obtain film industry standard image quality at high frame rates (for slow motion). We played with FumeFX and Elementacular for Maya to produce realistic evolving 3d rain clouds, used Optical Flares in AfterEffects to give it an epic anamorphic look, and graded the footage with DaVinci Resolve.'),(6930,645,'_main_content_area','field_5629ec918a334'),(6931,645,'single_image',''),(6932,645,'_single_image','field_5629ea2db47b2'),(6933,645,'header_image','633'),(6934,645,'_header_image','field_5629edc6a3424'),(6935,645,'standfirst_text','A young boy releases a cloud into a church and it builds to a storm. Elwood’s Ark traces the journey of the water we drink, back 13.8 billion years through time and space to the beginnings of the Universe, challenging our perceptions of religion and redemption.'),(6936,645,'_standfirst_text','field_5629ea6d8d729'),(6937,645,'vimeo_id','138625045'),(6938,645,'_vimeo_id','field_5629e91cf9252'),(6939,645,'vimeo_id_two',''),(6940,645,'_vimeo_id_two','field_564b0ac8ebbf4'),(6941,645,'youtube_id',''),(6942,645,'_youtube_id','field_5629e94ef9253'),(6943,645,'_','field_5629e968f9254'),(6944,6